headline: AppLovin (APP): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q1 Earnings?
summary: Over the past six months, AppLovin has been a great trade. While the S&P 500 was flat, the stock price has climbed by 8.9% to $368.04 per share. This was partly due to its solid quarterly results, and the run-up might have investors contemplating their next move.
